<h1 id="instalação-do-scilab">Instalação do Scilab</h1>
<p>Baixe o arquivo <kbd>.tar.gz</kbd>:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>wget http://www.scilab.org/download/6.0.1/scilab-6.0.1.bin.linux-x86_64.tar.gz
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Descompacte e copie para a pasta <kbd>~/.local</kbd> as pastas com seus respectivos arquivos.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>cp -a scilab-6.0.1/bin/* ~/.local/bin/
cp -a scilab-6.0.1/share/* ~/.local/share/
cp -a scilab-6.0.1/lib/* ~/.local/lib/
cp -a scilab-6.0.1/thirdparty/ ~/.local/thirdparty/
cp -a scilab-6.0.1/include/* ~/.local/include/
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>No arquivo <kbd>~/.bashrc</kbd> adiciona as linhas:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code># LIBRARY PATH FOR SCILAB
export LIBRARY_PATH=$LIBRARY_PATH:/home/marleson/.local/lib/scilab/
export LIBRARY_PATH=$LIBRARY_PATH:/home/marleson/.local/lib/thirdparty/
export LIBRARY_PATH=$LIBRARY_PATH:/home/marleson/.local/lib/pkgconfig/ PRONTO!
</code></pre></div></div>

<h1 id="change-layout-of-numeric-keyboard">CHANGE LAYOUT OF NUMERIC KEYBOARD</h1>
<p>You can change this behavior using the keyboard options settings :</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>System Settings -&gt; Keyboard -&gt; Layout -&gt; Options -&gt; 
-&gt; Layout of numeric -&gt; Numeric keypad delete key behavior -&gt; Legacy key with comma
</code></pre></div></div>

<h1 id="change-python-version">CHANGE PYTHON VERSION</h1>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sudo update-alternatives --config python3
</code></pre></div></div>

<h1 id="install-conda">INSTALL CONDA</h1>
<p>Download miniconda from: https://docs.conda.io/en/latest/miniconda.html<br />
Install as:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>bash Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="to-activate-the-envirement-type">To activate the envirement type:</h2>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>conda activate
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="to-deactive-the-envirement-type">To deactive the envirement type:</h2>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>conda deactivate
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="theres-a-conda-configuration-setting-to-disable-the-automatic-base-activation">There’s a conda configuration setting to disable the automatic base activation:</h3>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>conda config --set auto_activate_base false
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>The first time you run it, it’ll create a <kbd>./condarc</kbd> in your home directory with that setting to override the default.</p>

<p>This wouldn’t de-clutter your <kbd>.bash_profile</kbd> but it’s a cleaner solution without manual editing that section that conda manages.</p>

<h1 id="maple-13">MAPLE 13</h1>

<p>Use th following command to Install:</p>

<div class="language-sh highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sh Maple13LinuxX86_64Installer.bin
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>It is recommended to install in your home folder such as: <kbd>/home/$USER/maple13/</kbd></p>

<p>Copy the <kbd>license.dat</kbd> file to the license folder. In case of problems with the activation, make sure the <kbd>lmutil</kbd> file is executable in the <kbd>maple13/bin.X86_64_LINUX/</kbd> folder.</p>

<p>In this case, install the following package for compatibility:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>apt-get install gcc-multilib
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>FONTE: <a href="https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/75054/ldd-tells-me-my-app-is-not-a-dynamic-executable">https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/75054/ldd-tells-me-my-app-is-not-a-dynamic-executable</a></p>

